WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.446 align:middle line:90%
[SWOOSH]

00:00:01.446 --> 00:00:04.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:08.676 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.676 --> 00:00:10.610 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.610 --> 00:00:13.580 align:middle line:84%
>> I went through just a
tremendous fear of dying.

00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:15.560 align:middle line:84%
It seemed to spring
up out of nowhere,

00:00:15.560 --> 00:00:18.530 align:middle line:84%
and it just had me
secretly look for evidence

00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:20.460 align:middle line:90%
to believe in to rest my fears.

00:00:20.460 --> 00:00:22.670 align:middle line:84%
I started feeling like
there's so much more to life

00:00:22.670 --> 00:00:23.660 align:middle line:90%
than meets the eye.

00:00:23.660 --> 00:00:25.580 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you think
the afterlife is?

00:00:25.580 --> 00:00:27.650 align:middle line:84%
>> They're just vibrating
at a different energy,

00:00:27.650 --> 00:00:29.600 align:middle line:90%
but they're here right now.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:32.299 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we have left
undone here on Earth,

00:00:32.299 --> 00:00:33.650 align:middle line:90%
we can do on the other side.

00:00:33.650 --> 00:00:36.440 align:middle line:84%
I think our loved ones are busy,
but they're only a thought,

00:00:36.440 --> 00:00:37.970 align:middle line:90%
a heartbeat, a breath away.

00:00:37.970 --> 00:00:41.030 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, we are part
of a much bigger picture,

00:00:41.030 --> 00:00:42.590 align:middle line:90%
and we can never die.

00:00:42.590 --> 00:00:46.938 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.938 --> 00:00:48.980 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:48.980 --> 00:00:52.910 align:middle line:10%
In 1996, the fear of
dying led Sandra Champlain

00:00:52.910 --> 00:00:56.270 align:middle line:10%
on a journey to find
evidence of the afterlife.

00:00:56.270 --> 00:01:00.080 align:middle line:84%
She has spent 25 years
researching and eventually

00:01:00.080 --> 00:01:02.690 align:middle line:84%
sharing the truth that
she has uncovered,

00:01:02.690 --> 00:01:04.110 align:middle line:90%
which she'll share with us.

00:01:04.110 --> 00:01:07.070 align:middle line:84%
She is also the host of
the iHeartRadio podcast,

00:01:07.070 --> 00:01:10.590 align:middle line:84%
"Shades of the Afterlife,"
and author of the book,

00:01:10.590 --> 00:01:11.900 align:middle line:90%
"We Don't Die."

00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:13.580 align:middle line:84%
Sandra, welcome to
"Beyond Belief."

00:01:13.580 --> 00:01:14.390 align:middle line:84%
>>SANDRA CHAMPLAIN:
Oh, George, thank you.

00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:15.750 align:middle line:84%
I'm so happy to
be here with you.

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's great
seeing you again.

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:19.040 align:middle line:84%
I've talked to you so
many times on the radio,

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:21.230 align:middle line:84%
but it's good to see you
up front and personal.

00:01:21.230 --> 00:01:21.860 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Absolutely.

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:23.660 align:middle line:84%
Normally, it's in the middle
of the night for me, but--

00:01:23.660 --> 00:01:24.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It sure is.

00:01:24.410 --> 00:01:25.452 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --I love it.

00:01:25.452 --> 00:01:28.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You were once a
skeptic about all of this.

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:29.450 align:middle line:90%
What changed your mind?

00:01:29.450 --> 00:01:31.250 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah,
skeptic about all of it.

00:01:31.250 --> 00:01:34.310 align:middle line:10%
My dad-- very
scientifically minded,

00:01:34.310 --> 00:01:36.980 align:middle line:10%
and kids, you need to
see it to believe it,

00:01:36.980 --> 00:01:38.808 align:middle line:10%
that sort of attitude.

00:01:38.808 --> 00:01:40.850 align:middle line:10%
And then I went through
it just a tremendous fear

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:44.270 align:middle line:10%
of dying that seemed to
spring up out of nowhere,

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:47.690 align:middle line:10%
and it just had me
secretly look for evidence,

00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:50.450 align:middle line:10%
look for something to
believe in to rest my fears.

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:53.450 align:middle line:84%
So throughout my
journey, I started

00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:57.200 align:middle line:84%
having weird experiences like
psychic things happening to me.

00:01:57.200 --> 00:01:59.930 align:middle line:84%
I'd know a song before
it came on the radio.

00:01:59.930 --> 00:02:01.740 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, how
does that happen?

00:02:01.740 --> 00:02:02.540 align:middle line:90%
And so that--

00:02:02.540 --> 00:02:03.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were these
like messages,

00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:05.148 align:middle line:84%
people were trying to
tell you something?

00:02:05.148 --> 00:02:06.680 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: At that point, no.

00:02:06.680 --> 00:02:10.432 align:middle line:84%
But I'd hear "Love Me Tender"
in my brain, Elvis singing it,

00:02:10.432 --> 00:02:12.265 align:middle line:84%
and I'd turn on the
radio, and it was there.

00:02:12.265 --> 00:02:13.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: (IMPERSONATING
ELVIS) Thank you very much.

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:15.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: So it
was my first hint

00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:18.770 align:middle line:84%
that we are more than
we believe we are.

00:02:18.770 --> 00:02:21.860 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up taking
a course in mediumship,

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:24.710 align:middle line:84%
which I wanted to be
true, but I thought

00:02:24.710 --> 00:02:27.830 align:middle line:84%
things that seem to be too
good to be true usually

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:30.740 align:middle line:84%
are, and out of my own
head, could accurately

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:33.450 align:middle line:84%
tell people some details
about their loved ones.

00:02:33.450 --> 00:02:36.410 align:middle line:84%
And so I started feeling like
there's so much more to life

00:02:36.410 --> 00:02:37.520 align:middle line:90%
than meets the eye.

00:02:37.520 --> 00:02:39.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What was it
that began to start

00:02:39.770 --> 00:02:43.613 align:middle line:84%
changing your mind about
the skeptic to a believer?

00:02:43.613 --> 00:02:45.530 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Well, like
I said, the mediumship

00:02:45.530 --> 00:02:47.180 align:middle line:90%
was the very first part.

00:02:47.180 --> 00:02:50.720 align:middle line:84%
I had taken a course,
and with my eyes closed,

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:54.530 align:middle line:84%
I was told to use my
imagination and literally invent

00:02:54.530 --> 00:02:57.290 align:middle line:84%
someone standing behind the
partner I was working with--

00:02:57.290 --> 00:02:57.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:02:57.650 --> 00:02:59.858 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --because what
the instructor was saying

00:02:59.858 --> 00:03:00.920 align:middle line:90%
is this is just practice.

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:02.070 align:middle line:90%
We aren't really doing it.

00:03:02.070 --> 00:03:04.490 align:middle line:84%
So it took away all my
fears, and, of course, I'm

00:03:04.490 --> 00:03:06.830 align:middle line:90%
very creative, I think.

00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:10.110 align:middle line:84%
And so I invented a man
standing behind my partner.

00:03:10.110 --> 00:03:11.540 align:middle line:84%
With my eyes
closed, I said, it's

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:14.000 align:middle line:84%
your grandfather
on your mom's side.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:15.860 align:middle line:90%
He was a fisherman in Denmark.

00:03:15.860 --> 00:03:18.530 align:middle line:84%
My imagination gave
me a fishing boat.

00:03:18.530 --> 00:03:20.750 align:middle line:84%
I saw him puffing
away on a cigarette.

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:84%
I saw a big gap between
his two front teeth.

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:26.840 align:middle line:84%
I hear the name, Jan, and
that-- and the word, "Denmark,"

00:03:26.840 --> 00:03:27.800 align:middle line:90%
like he's from Denmark.

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:32.240 align:middle line:84%
And so I just shared what I
saw, and when I opened my eyes,

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:33.170 align:middle line:90%
she's crying.

00:03:33.170 --> 00:03:34.470 align:middle line:90%
Her grandfather's name was Jan.

00:03:34.470 --> 00:03:35.720 align:middle line:90%
He was a fisherman in Denmark.

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:36.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you
didn't know that?

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:37.130 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: None of it.

00:03:37.130 --> 00:03:37.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:38.958 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I never
even met this woman.

00:03:38.958 --> 00:03:43.760 align:middle line:84%
So that began the journey, and
then I stayed very, very quiet,

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:47.000 align:middle line:84%
and I got interested in
electronic voice phenomena by--

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:47.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: EVPs.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:51.320 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --watching things
on the computer, reading books,

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:55.850 align:middle line:84%
and lo and behold, I
took a course on EVPs.

00:03:55.850 --> 00:03:59.555 align:middle line:84%
And late at night, with
my digital tape recorder

00:03:59.555 --> 00:04:03.650 align:middle line:84%
is what I had, I was staying at
the Omega Center in Rhinebeck,

00:04:03.650 --> 00:04:05.690 align:middle line:84%
New York, and just
recording raindrops.

00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:11.750 align:middle line:84%
And I really wanted to come
forward and be honest to people

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.190 align:middle line:90%
that I believe in the afterlife.

00:04:13.190 --> 00:04:16.640 align:middle line:84%
But I was still so scared
what people would think of me.

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:19.130 align:middle line:84%
But I said to any loved
ones that were with me,

00:04:19.130 --> 00:04:20.810 align:middle line:84%
I said, if this
is real and I need

00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:23.450 align:middle line:84%
to share about the
reality of the afterlife,

00:04:23.450 --> 00:04:25.010 align:middle line:84%
I said, I need
you to try to talk

00:04:25.010 --> 00:04:26.610 align:middle line:90%
really loud into my microphone.

00:04:26.610 --> 00:04:27.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huh.

00:04:27.410 --> 00:04:29.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And then
I'll say good night.

00:04:29.160 --> 00:04:32.480 align:middle line:84%
And when I replayed
this short recording,

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:36.410 align:middle line:84%
it says, good night,
Sandra, in a man's voice.

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:38.780 align:middle line:84%
Two women whispered,
good night, good night.

00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:39.980 align:middle line:90%
And then another male--

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:41.490 align:middle line:90%
male's voice saying, good night.

00:04:41.490 --> 00:04:42.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:04:42.290 --> 00:04:45.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: So talk
about putting goosebumps

00:04:45.050 --> 00:04:48.080 align:middle line:84%
throughout me, but that
was the first thing

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:51.900 align:middle line:84%
that gave me, like,
tangible evidence, something

00:04:51.900 --> 00:04:52.700 align:middle line:90%
I could share.

00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:54.830 align:middle line:84%
And then from there, I
just started experimenting

00:04:54.830 --> 00:04:55.830 align:middle line:90%
and working with people.

00:04:55.830 --> 00:04:56.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And growing with it.

00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:57.855 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And
growing with it.

00:04:57.855 --> 00:05:00.380 align:middle line:84%
So not only could I see
people in my mind's eye,

00:05:00.380 --> 00:05:03.740 align:middle line:84%
but I was getting recordings
that were so special,

00:05:03.740 --> 00:05:05.420 align:middle line:90%
mostly "I love yous."

00:05:05.420 --> 00:05:06.260 align:middle line:90%
And then--

00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huh.

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:08.520 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, and then it--

00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:11.780 align:middle line:84%
now, I kept all of this
secret from most people,

00:05:11.780 --> 00:05:13.670 align:middle line:84%
because I really thought
people would think

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:15.260 align:middle line:90%
I would be a little strange.

00:05:15.260 --> 00:05:18.110 align:middle line:84%
So I collected all kinds
of really good information

00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:20.900 align:middle line:84%
about the afterlife,
feeling that someday, I'll

00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:22.923 align:middle line:90%
tell people, but just not now.

00:05:22.923 --> 00:05:24.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And look
what you're doing now.

00:05:24.590 --> 00:05:24.920 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah.

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:26.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Look what
you're doing now.

00:05:26.420 --> 00:05:29.090 align:middle line:84%
Sandra, in the Gaia series,
"Damanhur, A Journey

00:05:29.090 --> 00:05:32.210 align:middle line:84%
through Time,"
Crotalo Sesamo teaches

00:05:32.210 --> 00:05:35.450 align:middle line:84%
why synchronicity is
a fundamental source

00:05:35.450 --> 00:05:36.400 align:middle line:90%
of evolution.

00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:37.200 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:05:37.200 --> 00:05:42.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the evolution for us is
what I've been briefly describe

00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:46.420 align:middle line:84%
as the process of the
spiritualization of the matter.

00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:48.150 align:middle line:84%
In other-- in other
hands, it is what

00:05:48.150 --> 00:05:50.280 align:middle line:84%
is being called
the Enlightenment,

00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:52.590 align:middle line:84%
or again, in spiritual
physics is what we call also

00:05:52.590 --> 00:05:53.880 align:middle line:90%
metamorphosis.

00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:58.350 align:middle line:84%
And it's literally to bring
the matter to become light,

00:05:58.350 --> 00:06:00.840 align:middle line:84%
to bring the form
to become energy.

00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:03.720 align:middle line:84%
It's everything that
is born to the idea

00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:06.300 align:middle line:84%
that the form could be
transformed in something

00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:08.100 align:middle line:90%
that we call spirit.

00:06:08.100 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, but complexity,
it's now very interesting

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:16.710 align:middle line:84%
to help us to understand how
synchronicity, it's bonding

00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:18.730 align:middle line:90%
all these different events.

00:06:18.730 --> 00:06:21.390 align:middle line:84%
So we can truly
say that everything

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:25.140 align:middle line:84%
that is happening, so all
these events that are not

00:06:25.140 --> 00:06:30.270 align:middle line:84%
based on cause/effect, but
on synchronicity, are guided,

00:06:30.270 --> 00:06:34.950 align:middle line:84%
are drawn to a higher
level of evolution.

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:37.680 align:middle line:84%
So I like to imagine that the
universal form is immersed

00:06:37.680 --> 00:06:40.830 align:middle line:84%
in something that is
literally pulling or pushing,

00:06:40.830 --> 00:06:44.340 align:middle line:84%
if you like, everything
in a direction

00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:47.280 align:middle line:84%
of spiritualized
matter to transform

00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:48.930 align:middle line:90%
the matter into light.

00:06:48.930 --> 00:06:53.670 align:middle line:84%
So everything is pulled
to become more evolved.

00:06:53.670 --> 00:06:57.990 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, we are still talking
about a field of possibilities

00:06:57.990 --> 00:07:00.330 align:middle line:84%
because we don't have
to forget that we have

00:07:00.330 --> 00:07:03.270 align:middle line:84%
a very important other element
that we've been introduced

00:07:03.270 --> 00:07:05.400 align:middle line:90%
that is called the free will.

00:07:05.400 --> 00:07:08.700 align:middle line:84%
And the free will is
always the possibility

00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:13.530 align:middle line:84%
to evolve or to evolve fast
or also not to evolve, to stop

00:07:13.530 --> 00:07:14.980 align:middle line:90%
or even to go back.

00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:15.780 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:15.780 --> 00:07:18.970 align:middle line:84%
So free will is the
power of our choices.

00:07:18.970 --> 00:07:23.295 align:middle line:84%
So we don't have to forget that
we are the masters of our life,

00:07:23.295 --> 00:07:25.920 align:middle line:84%
and we don't have to forget that
all of these possibility, they

00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:28.300 align:middle line:84%
could be used in
many different way.

00:07:28.300 --> 00:07:31.620 align:middle line:84%
This is the reason why, also
in the perception of the event,

00:07:31.620 --> 00:07:34.260 align:middle line:84%
something for me could
be extremely positive,

00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:37.410 align:middle line:84%
and the same exact
situation for another person

00:07:37.410 --> 00:07:39.360 align:middle line:90%
could be felt exactly negative.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:41.880 align:middle line:84%
So synchronicity
is moving events

00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:44.550 align:middle line:84%
thanks to the
complexity, to what

00:07:44.550 --> 00:07:46.350 align:middle line:84%
we call the error
of complexity, so

00:07:46.350 --> 00:07:49.727 align:middle line:84%
the error of evolution, that
is pulling us to change.

00:07:49.727 --> 00:07:50.560 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:52.200 align:middle line:84%
I've always been
fascinated, Sandra,

00:07:52.200 --> 00:07:55.440 align:middle line:84%
by these thinkers who
come up with these things.

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:56.310 align:middle line:90%
Fascinating.

00:07:56.310 --> 00:07:57.330 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Brilliant.

00:07:57.330 --> 00:07:59.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What does
"synchronicity" mean to you?

00:07:59.460 --> 00:08:01.980 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: My dad would say
it's God's way of remaining

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:05.253 align:middle line:84%
anonymous, and I love
that because as a human--

00:08:05.253 --> 00:08:06.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting phrase.

00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:08.250 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah,
whether you believe

00:08:08.250 --> 00:08:11.160 align:middle line:84%
in God, the universe,
higher power, I think we're

00:08:11.160 --> 00:08:13.080 align:middle line:84%
only shown just what
we need in our life.

00:08:13.080 --> 00:08:15.570 align:middle line:84%
We get these little
trails to follow,

00:08:15.570 --> 00:08:18.480 align:middle line:84%
and I can't tell you how many
airplane trips I have been

00:08:18.480 --> 00:08:21.760 align:middle line:90%
on, where if I'm--

00:08:21.760 --> 00:08:24.460 align:middle line:84%
got the courage to say hello
to the next person sitting next

00:08:24.460 --> 00:08:26.710 align:middle line:84%
to me, they're either
coming from a funeral,

00:08:26.710 --> 00:08:28.000 align:middle line:90%
they've had a loved one pass--

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:28.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:08:28.390 --> 00:08:30.057 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --they
had a fear of dying,

00:08:30.057 --> 00:08:31.599 align:middle line:84%
so I've had a lot
of synchronicities.

00:08:31.599 --> 00:08:33.307 align:middle line:84%
And I just travel with
a copy of my book.

00:08:33.307 --> 00:08:35.789 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, so have they,
then, to be put next to you.

00:08:35.789 --> 00:08:36.789 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Absolutely.

00:08:36.789 --> 00:08:37.299 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:08:37.299 --> 00:08:38.799 align:middle line:84%
I don't take it
lightly, and I feel

00:08:38.799 --> 00:08:41.049 align:middle line:84%
like human beings
have to trust where

00:08:41.049 --> 00:08:44.650 align:middle line:84%
we are today in this very moment
is just where we need to be.

00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:47.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sometimes people
say synchronicities

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:50.230 align:middle line:84%
replace coincidences,
which I don't believe in.

00:08:50.230 --> 00:08:52.780 align:middle line:84%
I think things happen
for a reason, don't you?

00:08:52.780 --> 00:08:56.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I think things
happen for a reason generally.

00:08:56.450 --> 00:08:58.630 align:middle line:84%
But I think there's some
really horrific things that

00:08:58.630 --> 00:09:02.230 align:middle line:84%
can happen, and
I know that if we

00:09:02.230 --> 00:09:04.720 align:middle line:84%
can look at that situation--
what did I learn from it?

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:06.170 align:middle line:90%
What am I taking away?

00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:07.780 align:middle line:90%
How can I help another person?

00:09:07.780 --> 00:09:10.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who manifests
these things to happen?

00:09:10.340 --> 00:09:12.850 align:middle line:84%
Do we do it, or is there
something out there

00:09:12.850 --> 00:09:13.990 align:middle line:90%
that makes it done?

00:09:13.990 --> 00:09:16.720 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: What I
say to empower myself,

00:09:16.720 --> 00:09:20.230 align:middle line:84%
because I think each one of
us has to find our own truths,

00:09:20.230 --> 00:09:24.460 align:middle line:84%
is that we came into this
Earth on our own free will.

00:09:24.460 --> 00:09:26.620 align:middle line:84%
There's stuff to learn
here that we're not

00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:28.420 align:middle line:90%
going to learn anywhere else.

00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:30.440 align:middle line:90%
We have emotions.

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:32.920 align:middle line:90%
We have flesh and bones.

00:09:32.920 --> 00:09:33.880 align:middle line:90%
We can hug people.

00:09:33.880 --> 00:09:35.260 align:middle line:90%
We can taste things.

00:09:35.260 --> 00:09:39.490 align:middle line:84%
And we choose what our
life's path is going to be,

00:09:39.490 --> 00:09:42.070 align:middle line:84%
not down to every
small interaction,

00:09:42.070 --> 00:09:45.170 align:middle line:84%
but the general things we
want to learn in our life.

00:09:45.170 --> 00:09:45.970 align:middle line:90%
So I think we do.

00:09:45.970 --> 00:09:49.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So Sandra, what was
your aha moment where you

00:09:49.300 --> 00:09:52.100 align:middle line:84%
really realized, I
have a mission here--

00:09:52.100 --> 00:09:53.690 align:middle line:90%
I have a purpose here?

00:09:53.690 --> 00:09:54.490 align:middle line:90%
What was it?

00:09:54.490 --> 00:09:58.720 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: It was after
seeing a movie called "50/50"

00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:00.160 align:middle line:90%
that was about--

00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:03.510 align:middle line:90%
well, it was called a comedy.

00:10:03.510 --> 00:10:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And at that point,
my dad had passed.

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:07.910 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:10:07.910 --> 00:10:08.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sorry to hear that.

00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:09.628 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Thank you.

00:10:09.628 --> 00:10:11.255 align:middle line:84%
Enough time has
passed, so I don't

00:10:11.255 --> 00:10:13.380 align:middle line:84%
say time heals all wounds,
but it certainly makes--

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:13.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It helps.

00:10:13.740 --> 00:10:14.565 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --the
journey easier.

00:10:14.565 --> 00:10:15.365 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It helps.

00:10:15.365 --> 00:10:19.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: But I had collected
so much about the afterlife,

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:23.160 align:middle line:84%
and I also collected a lot
about the grieving process

00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:25.200 align:middle line:90%
and why it has to hurt so much.

00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:27.510 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't
handle the thoughts

00:10:27.510 --> 00:10:29.790 align:middle line:84%
in my own head that
were saying, Sandra,

00:10:29.790 --> 00:10:31.470 align:middle line:84%
you've got to tell
people about this.

00:10:31.470 --> 00:10:33.810 align:middle line:90%
You can really help humanity.

00:10:33.810 --> 00:10:36.420 align:middle line:84%
But fear can really
cripple people,

00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:41.070 align:middle line:84%
so I take myself to the movies
to get my mind off everything,

00:10:41.070 --> 00:10:45.630 align:middle line:84%
and this particular movie
had some comedy moments,

00:10:45.630 --> 00:10:48.180 align:middle line:84%
but it was a story of a
young man getting cancer,

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:51.960 align:middle line:84%
going through chemotherapy
treatments, his friends dying,

00:10:51.960 --> 00:10:53.520 align:middle line:90%
and it was about grief.

00:10:53.520 --> 00:10:58.680 align:middle line:84%
So I got into my car with
tears running down my face,

00:10:58.680 --> 00:11:02.940 align:middle line:84%
and for the very first
time, had my new iPhone--

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:04.800 align:middle line:84%
never used the
camera, and I just

00:11:04.800 --> 00:11:08.850 align:middle line:84%
felt like making a confession--
and held the camera to my face

00:11:08.850 --> 00:11:12.630 align:middle line:84%
and told a 20-minute
story of my journey

00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:15.780 align:middle line:84%
and that this is the
moment I need to share.

00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:18.270 align:middle line:84%
Now, George, I was never going
to show anybody that film.

00:11:18.270 --> 00:11:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You just
wanted a record it.

00:11:19.590 --> 00:11:21.330 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I just wanted
to get it off my chest.

00:11:21.330 --> 00:11:21.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:11:21.720 --> 00:11:23.595 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And didn't
a friend of mine call

00:11:23.595 --> 00:11:25.470 align:middle line:90%
and say her dad had passed.

00:11:25.470 --> 00:11:26.370 align:middle line:90%
What do I know?

00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't have the time to
really talk to her, so I said,

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:31.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to send
you this video,

00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:33.150 align:middle line:84%
but don't share it
with anyone else.

00:11:33.150 --> 00:11:34.483 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That you just recorded.

00:11:34.483 --> 00:11:36.240 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And I
did, and she went off

00:11:36.240 --> 00:11:39.330 align:middle line:84%
to share it with two friends
and two friends and two friends,

00:11:39.330 --> 00:11:40.620 align:middle line:90%
and it just grew.

00:11:40.620 --> 00:11:43.230 align:middle line:84%
And the difference that
it made and people chose--

00:11:43.230 --> 00:11:44.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did it
make social network?

00:11:44.730 --> 00:11:45.030 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yes.

00:11:45.030 --> 00:11:45.830 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It did.

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.460 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: It did,
and people chose

00:11:47.460 --> 00:11:50.460 align:middle line:84%
not to take their own
lives because of it.

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:53.010 align:middle line:84%
People changed
their relationships.

00:11:53.010 --> 00:11:55.230 align:middle line:84%
People had faith
in the afterlife,

00:11:55.230 --> 00:11:57.900 align:middle line:84%
and that's when I thought,
I'm the one for this mission.

00:11:57.900 --> 00:12:00.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Was your
dad very influential

00:12:00.270 --> 00:12:01.590 align:middle line:90%
in some of this for you?

00:12:01.590 --> 00:12:04.860 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: He was, and
he was very religious.

00:12:04.860 --> 00:12:06.360 align:middle line:90%
He went to church every day.

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:06.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:12:06.820 --> 00:12:07.530 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: So I was--

00:12:07.530 --> 00:12:08.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Every day?

00:12:08.330 --> 00:12:10.800 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Every day, so
I was afraid to tell him

00:12:10.800 --> 00:12:13.530 align:middle line:84%
that I'd been on this secret
search of the afterlife.

00:12:13.530 --> 00:12:17.130 align:middle line:84%
But before he passed, I felt
like I needed to tell him

00:12:17.130 --> 00:12:18.570 align:middle line:90%
what was in my heart.

00:12:18.570 --> 00:12:21.750 align:middle line:84%
So I told him about some of the
medium courses that I've done

00:12:21.750 --> 00:12:23.700 align:middle line:84%
and some of the things,
and he looked at me

00:12:23.700 --> 00:12:26.235 align:middle line:84%
with big brown eyes like,
you've got-- you know,

00:12:26.235 --> 00:12:27.990 align:middle line:84%
he wanted to
believe me, but this

00:12:27.990 --> 00:12:29.520 align:middle line:90%
was a little far out there.

00:12:29.520 --> 00:12:32.760 align:middle line:84%
And in a moment,
in my mind, I saw

00:12:32.760 --> 00:12:36.090 align:middle line:84%
a yellow Piper Cub
airplane, tail dragger,

00:12:36.090 --> 00:12:38.190 align:middle line:90%
with black letters on it.

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:41.830 align:middle line:84%
And I felt, in my heart,
a man laughing, saying,

00:12:41.830 --> 00:12:44.340 align:middle line:84%
I did get to take
my toys with me.

00:12:44.340 --> 00:12:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, Dad, I'm
going to tell you this.

00:12:46.780 --> 00:12:48.240 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
it means anything.

00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And just the month
before, his good friend,

00:12:50.970 --> 00:12:54.270 align:middle line:84%
who was a pilot who owned
that particular airplane,

00:12:54.270 --> 00:12:56.130 align:middle line:90%
had a conversation with my dad.

00:12:56.130 --> 00:12:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And Dad had told him, you've
got a fight for your life.

00:12:58.980 --> 00:13:01.020 align:middle line:84%
You can beat cancer
because you don't

00:13:01.020 --> 00:13:02.580 align:middle line:90%
get to take your toys with you.

00:13:02.580 --> 00:13:03.943 align:middle line:90%
And Dad wanted to know--

00:13:03.943 --> 00:13:04.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Great advice.

00:13:04.860 --> 00:13:08.130 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --everything that
I knew about the afterlife,

00:13:08.130 --> 00:13:10.860 align:middle line:84%
and he made me promise
I'd write a book.

00:13:10.860 --> 00:13:12.670 align:middle line:90%
And here we are today.

00:13:12.670 --> 00:13:14.642 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And here's the
book, "We Don't Die."

00:13:14.642 --> 00:13:16.100 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: A
skeptic's discovery.

00:13:16.100 --> 00:13:17.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you
dedicate this to Dad?

00:13:17.780 --> 00:13:19.197 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I
did, and to my mom.

00:13:19.197 --> 00:13:20.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's what I thought.

00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:21.290 align:middle line:90%
Well, good for you.

00:13:21.290 --> 00:13:22.123 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Thanks.

00:13:22.123 --> 00:13:24.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think the afterlife is?

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:25.710 align:middle line:90%
What does it mean to you?

00:13:25.710 --> 00:13:29.630 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Ah, I think it's
a place right within where

00:13:29.630 --> 00:13:30.560 align:middle line:90%
we are right now.

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:32.040 align:middle line:90%
I think we are part of it.

00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:33.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Always was?

00:13:33.170 --> 00:13:36.110 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, I don't
think it's out there somewhere.

00:13:36.110 --> 00:13:38.930 align:middle line:84%
I don't think heaven
is beyond the clouds.

00:13:38.930 --> 00:13:42.950 align:middle line:84%
I think mediums and people
that can connect with people

00:13:42.950 --> 00:13:45.050 align:middle line:84%
can because they're
just vibrating

00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:46.490 align:middle line:90%
at a different energy.

00:13:46.490 --> 00:13:48.660 align:middle line:90%
But they're here right now.

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:50.090 align:middle line:84%
So around us right
now, we've got

00:13:50.090 --> 00:13:52.220 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of wireless
signals going on,

00:13:52.220 --> 00:13:54.270 align:middle line:84%
and energy can live
in the same place

00:13:54.270 --> 00:13:56.670 align:middle line:84%
at the same time, different
sources of energy.

00:13:56.670 --> 00:13:59.300 align:middle line:84%
So there's no reason our
loved ones can't be here,

00:13:59.300 --> 00:14:01.260 align:middle line:90%
right here, right now as well.

00:14:01.260 --> 00:14:03.710 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very close to
what we have here on Earth,

00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:06.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm hoping without
the mosquitoes.

00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:09.020 align:middle line:84%
But I think we communicate
with our thoughts.

00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:10.655 align:middle line:84%
From everything
I've investigated--

00:14:10.655 --> 00:14:11.488 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:14:11.488 --> 00:14:13.610 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --we can
pick our favorite age,

00:14:13.610 --> 00:14:18.330 align:middle line:84%
we're of good health, but it's
a land much like we experience.

00:14:18.330 --> 00:14:19.470 align:middle line:90%
It's not too different.

00:14:19.470 --> 00:14:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And I think we can progress
to different things,

00:14:21.950 --> 00:14:23.780 align:middle line:84%
but we need to go to
a place where we feel

00:14:23.780 --> 00:14:25.700 align:middle line:90%
comfortable right off the bat.

00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:27.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look
at the teachings

00:14:27.440 --> 00:14:31.746 align:middle line:84%
of Ram Dass, who wants to
talk about the art of grief.

00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:32.620 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:14:32.620 --> 00:14:35.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Subtle thing about grief
is where people feel that if I

00:14:35.290 --> 00:14:38.860 align:middle line:84%
stop grieving, I am betraying
the person or the thing that

00:14:38.860 --> 00:14:42.850 align:middle line:84%
left because I'm forgetting,
and I must remember,

00:14:42.850 --> 00:14:45.790 align:middle line:90%
or else I wasn't a true lover.

00:14:45.790 --> 00:14:47.770 align:middle line:84%
The extraordinary
thing about it is

00:14:47.770 --> 00:14:52.630 align:middle line:84%
that as you quiet down from
the active process of grieving,

00:14:52.630 --> 00:14:56.950 align:middle line:84%
you quiet down, and
you listen, and you

00:14:56.950 --> 00:15:00.790 align:middle line:84%
begin to appreciate that
the way in which you

00:15:00.790 --> 00:15:05.620 align:middle line:84%
are with another person
in love exists independent

00:15:05.620 --> 00:15:08.950 align:middle line:84%
of coming and going,
even independent of death

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:11.930 align:middle line:90%
and all of those things.

00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:13.560 align:middle line:84%
Ramana Maharshi,
the sage, said when

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:16.770 align:middle line:84%
he was dying of cancer
and everybody said to him,

00:15:16.770 --> 00:15:18.730 align:middle line:84%
Bhagavan, Bhagavan,
don't leave us.

00:15:18.730 --> 00:15:19.530 align:middle line:90%
Don't leave us.

00:15:19.530 --> 00:15:20.400 align:middle line:90%
And he looked confused.

00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:21.480 align:middle line:90%
He says, don't be silly.

00:15:21.480 --> 00:15:23.820 align:middle line:90%
Where could I go?

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:25.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm just
dropping a body.

00:15:25.200 --> 00:15:28.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going anywhere.

00:15:28.540 --> 00:15:30.570 align:middle line:84%
And so you realize
that the grieving

00:15:30.570 --> 00:15:35.760 align:middle line:84%
is part of the dramatic
storyline of your separateness

00:15:35.760 --> 00:15:37.380 align:middle line:84%
because you can't
grieve for something

00:15:37.380 --> 00:15:38.697 align:middle line:90%
that didn't go anywhere.

00:15:38.697 --> 00:15:39.530 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:15:39.530 --> 00:15:41.170 align:middle line:90%
"I'm just dropping the body.

00:15:41.170 --> 00:15:42.182 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going anywhere."

00:15:42.182 --> 00:15:43.390 align:middle line:90%
That's fascinating, isn't it?

00:15:43.390 --> 00:15:44.770 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: That's beautiful.

00:15:44.770 --> 00:15:45.790 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That tells you a lot.

00:15:45.790 --> 00:15:46.665 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: It does.

00:15:46.665 --> 00:15:49.160 align:middle line:90%
Grief is awful.

00:15:49.160 --> 00:15:50.442 align:middle line:90%
It is the most painful thing--

00:15:50.442 --> 00:15:51.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's horrible.

00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:53.067 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --any
human being, I think,

00:15:53.067 --> 00:15:54.220 align:middle line:90%
will have to deal with.

00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:56.320 align:middle line:84%
The more we love,
the more it hurts.

00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:58.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it comes
in waves, doesn't it?

00:15:58.420 --> 00:16:00.190 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: The
waves are so painful,

00:16:00.190 --> 00:16:02.470 align:middle line:84%
and we literally have
to ride the wave.

00:16:02.470 --> 00:16:04.400 align:middle line:90%
What we resist persists.

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:05.780 align:middle line:90%
So go with it.

00:16:05.780 --> 00:16:09.970 align:middle line:84%
But our brain body is trying
to get used to a new reality

00:16:09.970 --> 00:16:11.750 align:middle line:90%
without that person.

00:16:11.750 --> 00:16:13.840 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm-- everything
I'm talking about as far

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:17.410 align:middle line:84%
as the afterlife, the foundation
of everything is helping people

00:16:17.410 --> 00:16:21.850 align:middle line:84%
through grief, but I think grief
can be very powerful to get us

00:16:21.850 --> 00:16:26.240 align:middle line:84%
to go on our spiritual journeys
and ask those big questions--

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:27.250 align:middle line:90%
what is life for?

00:16:27.250 --> 00:16:28.150 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:16:28.150 --> 00:16:31.210 align:middle line:84%
And I have found
more times than not,

00:16:31.210 --> 00:16:34.870 align:middle line:84%
either grief can kind
of kill somebody inside,

00:16:34.870 --> 00:16:38.200 align:middle line:84%
and they stop living, or it
can put them on this journey,

00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:40.363 align:middle line:84%
and they can embrace
the miraculous.

00:16:40.363 --> 00:16:42.280 align:middle line:84%
All these things about
the afterlife are real.

00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:44.728 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you convince
a skeptic or a non-believer--

00:16:44.728 --> 00:16:45.770 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Now that's--

00:16:45.770 --> 00:16:47.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --about the afterlife?

00:16:47.260 --> 00:16:48.680 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: That's tricky.

00:16:48.680 --> 00:16:51.100 align:middle line:84%
I don't think you can
convince anybody of anything.

00:16:51.100 --> 00:16:53.030 align:middle line:90%
People have to be open.

00:16:53.030 --> 00:16:54.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They have to want it.

00:16:54.280 --> 00:16:55.697 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: They
have to want it.

00:16:55.697 --> 00:16:58.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's little
breadcrumbs we can leave like,

00:16:58.690 --> 00:17:02.150 align:middle line:84%
hmm, what do you
think about this show?

00:17:02.150 --> 00:17:04.630 align:middle line:84%
What-- do you listen
to "Coast to Coast AM"?

00:17:04.630 --> 00:17:06.430 align:middle line:84%
What do you think
about this and that?

00:17:06.430 --> 00:17:08.170 align:middle line:84%
And you get people
into conversations,

00:17:08.170 --> 00:17:11.050 align:middle line:84%
and you realize whether
they're open or they're not.

00:17:11.050 --> 00:17:13.210 align:middle line:84%
I think people
that are not open,

00:17:13.210 --> 00:17:17.060 align:middle line:84%
we shouldn't even try to
push our beliefs on them.

00:17:17.060 --> 00:17:19.240 align:middle line:84%
I think we should
still share who we are

00:17:19.240 --> 00:17:21.849 align:middle line:84%
and what we believe in and
have confidence in that,

00:17:21.849 --> 00:17:23.260 align:middle line:90%
but never really try to push.

00:17:23.260 --> 00:17:26.290 align:middle line:84%
There will be a day that I
think every human being starts

00:17:26.290 --> 00:17:27.640 align:middle line:90%
asking these questions.

00:17:27.640 --> 00:17:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And when they're
ready, here we are.

00:17:29.200 --> 00:17:31.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sandra, have
you collected evidence

00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:35.200 align:middle line:84%
about the other side, where
you can just show somebody

00:17:35.200 --> 00:17:36.580 align:middle line:90%
and say, look at this?

00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:40.510 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I have, and
I've got YouTube videos

00:17:40.510 --> 00:17:42.340 align:middle line:84%
that I talk about the
10 reasons to believe

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:45.790 align:middle line:84%
in the afterlife, all coming
from my skeptical mind--

00:17:45.790 --> 00:17:49.360 align:middle line:84%
not pushing it on anyone,
but this is my journey.

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:53.250 align:middle line:84%
We human beings want
to believe, but we're

00:17:53.250 --> 00:17:55.920 align:middle line:84%
so afraid what other
people will think.

00:17:55.920 --> 00:17:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And there's a great quote
by Arthur Schopenhauer,

00:17:59.550 --> 00:18:03.570 align:middle line:90%
great philosophy from years ago.

00:18:03.570 --> 00:18:07.690 align:middle line:84%
He said, "All truth passes
through three stages.

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:09.750 align:middle line:90%
First, it is ridiculed.

00:18:09.750 --> 00:18:12.750 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, it is
violently opposed.

00:18:12.750 --> 00:18:16.392 align:middle line:84%
Third, it becomes
realized as self-evident."

00:18:16.392 --> 00:18:18.600 align:middle line:84%
So when you think of people
like the Wright brothers,

00:18:18.600 --> 00:18:21.780 align:middle line:84%
people laughed at them, their
dream of a flying machine.

00:18:21.780 --> 00:18:24.550 align:middle line:84%
People really violently
opposed what they were doing,

00:18:24.550 --> 00:18:25.350 align:middle line:90%
and then look.

00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:25.930 align:middle line:90%
Here we are--

00:18:25.930 --> 00:18:26.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How'd you get here?

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:27.810 align:middle line:84%
On a Wright brothers
plane, right?

00:18:27.810 --> 00:18:28.685 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Exactly.

00:18:28.685 --> 00:18:31.650 align:middle line:84%
So I think the same thing will
happen with the afterlife.

00:18:31.650 --> 00:18:35.130 align:middle line:84%
Someday, we'll be looking
back, and we won't even

00:18:35.130 --> 00:18:38.130 align:middle line:84%
believe that there was a time
where mankind didn't know

00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:39.480 align:middle line:90%
the truth about the afterlife.

00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:42.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think the
afterlife came before life?

00:18:42.160 --> 00:18:43.785 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Ah,
that's a big question.

00:18:43.785 --> 00:18:44.618 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It is huge.

00:18:44.618 --> 00:18:45.900 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I think so.

00:18:45.900 --> 00:18:48.820 align:middle line:90%
I like to see it as a game.

00:18:48.820 --> 00:18:49.620 align:middle line:90%
I--

00:18:49.620 --> 00:18:51.162 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or maybe
developed together?

00:18:51.162 --> 00:18:54.370 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Maybe developed
together, but for heaven,

00:18:54.370 --> 00:18:56.370 align:middle line:84%
for the afterlife, whatever
you want to call it,

00:18:56.370 --> 00:19:00.210 align:middle line:84%
if it really is all
good all of the time,

00:19:00.210 --> 00:19:03.120 align:middle line:84%
I would think that would
get tremendously boring.

00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:06.960 align:middle line:84%
But not only that-- to come
to a place where there's good

00:19:06.960 --> 00:19:13.560 align:middle line:84%
and bad, joy versus sadness,
all of those opposites is where

00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:16.973 align:middle line:84%
our soul can really truly
learn because if you--

00:19:16.973 --> 00:19:18.640 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
your favorite food is.

00:19:18.640 --> 00:19:20.370 align:middle line:84%
But if that's all you
got all your life--

00:19:20.370 --> 00:19:21.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Turkey and
mashed potatoes.

00:19:21.510 --> 00:19:22.785 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Turkey
and mashed potatoes.

00:19:22.785 --> 00:19:23.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I love it.

00:19:23.280 --> 00:19:24.240 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: A little
cranberry sauce maybe?

00:19:24.240 --> 00:19:26.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I only have it
once a year, but I love it.

00:19:26.050 --> 00:19:28.383 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: But if every
single day, three meals a day,

00:19:28.383 --> 00:19:30.935 align:middle line:84%
that's what you got, it
might get a little boring.

00:19:30.935 --> 00:19:32.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, a lot boring.

00:19:32.590 --> 00:19:35.750 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, but come to
a place called Planet Earth,

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:37.490 align:middle line:84%
and you can taste
the rainbow, George.

00:19:37.490 --> 00:19:39.555 align:middle line:84%
We've got all kinds
of great things.

00:19:39.555 --> 00:19:40.430 align:middle line:90%
But here's the thing.

00:19:40.430 --> 00:19:42.480 align:middle line:84%
You're going to forget
who you really are.

00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:44.630 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's
why we're here.

00:19:44.630 --> 00:19:47.810 align:middle line:84%
But ultimately, we are part
of a much bigger picture,

00:19:47.810 --> 00:19:49.225 align:middle line:90%
and we can never die.

00:19:49.225 --> 00:19:50.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why do so
many people, though,

00:19:50.850 --> 00:19:53.750 align:middle line:84%
have a difficulty
believing in the afterlife?

00:19:53.750 --> 00:19:57.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you go out and poll
people, I bet at least half

00:19:57.200 --> 00:19:58.580 align:middle line:84%
would say, I don't
believe in it.

00:19:58.580 --> 00:19:59.750 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I don't
think it's half.

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:00.860 align:middle line:90%
I think it's a lot less.

00:20:00.860 --> 00:20:04.520 align:middle line:10%
I think more people have a
fear of sharing their belief.

00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:06.770 align:middle line:10%
Almost everybody has
had a moment where

00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:09.260 align:middle line:10%
they know the telephone is
going to ring, and then it does,

00:20:09.260 --> 00:20:11.210 align:middle line:10%
or they're with somebody,
and they say the same thing

00:20:11.210 --> 00:20:12.140 align:middle line:10%
at the same time.

00:20:12.140 --> 00:20:15.710 align:middle line:84%
They're like, we must be tuned
into the same wavelength.

00:20:15.710 --> 00:20:18.020 align:middle line:84%
There's something that
people can't put their finger

00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:20.780 align:middle line:84%
on that's happened,
and I think more people

00:20:20.780 --> 00:20:22.070 align:middle line:90%
believe than don't believe.

00:20:22.070 --> 00:20:25.970 align:middle line:84%
But there's a huge fear
of, what will people think

00:20:25.970 --> 00:20:27.750 align:middle line:90%
if they know I believe in this?

00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.592 align:middle line:84%
So people just keep
their mouths shut.

00:20:29.592 --> 00:20:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Medium James
Van Praagh had a chance

00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:35.450 align:middle line:84%
to talk with Lisa Garr on
the show, "Inspirations."

00:20:35.450 --> 00:20:36.300 align:middle line:90%
He's one of a kind.

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:37.100 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: He is.

00:20:37.100 --> 00:20:37.900 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:42.350 align:middle line:10%
>> When somebody crosses
over or moves on as spirit,

00:20:42.350 --> 00:20:45.680 align:middle line:10%
do they really want to come
through and communicate with

00:20:45.680 --> 00:20:48.650 align:middle line:10%
the person who is still on this
Earth plane when they really

00:20:48.650 --> 00:20:52.710 align:middle line:10%
have an attachment to someone,
like losing a father or a child

00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:53.510 align:middle line:10%
even?

00:20:53.510 --> 00:20:56.052 align:middle line:10%
>> Just like the movie, "Ghost,"
which I think is a wonderful

00:20:56.052 --> 00:20:57.650 align:middle line:10%
depiction of the
way it really is,

00:20:57.650 --> 00:21:00.920 align:middle line:10%
when you leave this physical
shell, which is very painless--

00:21:00.920 --> 00:21:03.110 align:middle line:10%
there's no pain involved
with leaving the body,

00:21:03.110 --> 00:21:04.070 align:middle line:10%
no pain whatsoever.

00:21:04.070 --> 00:21:05.570 align:middle line:10%
Leading up to the
death, there might

00:21:05.570 --> 00:21:08.870 align:middle line:10%
be some pain about the
type of way you pass out.

00:21:08.870 --> 00:21:10.700 align:middle line:84%
But when you actually
leave, the spirit

00:21:10.700 --> 00:21:12.600 align:middle line:84%
leaves the physical
body, there is no pain.

00:21:12.600 --> 00:21:14.392 align:middle line:84%
And one of the first
things they want to do

00:21:14.392 --> 00:21:16.020 align:middle line:84%
is to tell their
loved ones, I'm OK.

00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:16.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm alive.

00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:17.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine.

00:21:17.730 --> 00:21:19.100 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to grieve.

00:21:19.100 --> 00:21:20.390 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to upset--

00:21:20.390 --> 00:21:22.880 align:middle line:84%
be upset about my death,
because I'm not dead.

00:21:22.880 --> 00:21:24.085 align:middle line:90%
I'm very alive.

00:21:24.085 --> 00:21:25.460 align:middle line:84%
And they'll go to
their funerals.

00:21:25.460 --> 00:21:27.770 align:middle line:84%
They all go to their funerals,
their memorial services.

00:21:27.770 --> 00:21:30.020 align:middle line:84%
They'll see who's standing
in the funeral at a chapel

00:21:30.020 --> 00:21:31.130 align:middle line:90%
there all the time.

00:21:31.130 --> 00:21:33.547 align:middle line:10%
>> I can imagine that would
be healing because if you have

00:21:33.547 --> 00:21:36.320 align:middle line:10%
someone who maybe died a
painful death or a disease

00:21:36.320 --> 00:21:39.380 align:middle line:10%
or an illness, and you watched
their physical body go through

00:21:39.380 --> 00:21:43.730 align:middle line:10%
such pain, to imagine them
no longer in that pain is--

00:21:43.730 --> 00:21:44.853 align:middle line:10%
it takes a leap of faith.

00:21:44.853 --> 00:21:47.270 align:middle line:10%
>> It does, but many times
when the spirit will come back,

00:21:47.270 --> 00:21:50.180 align:middle line:10%
they'll say, Mom, please
don't remember me that way.

00:21:50.180 --> 00:21:51.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm not in that car crash.

00:21:51.470 --> 00:21:55.270 align:middle line:84%
Mom, that's not my body like
that that's withered and dried

00:21:55.270 --> 00:21:56.070 align:middle line:90%
up like that.

00:21:56.070 --> 00:21:57.140 align:middle line:90%
That's not who I am.

00:21:57.140 --> 00:21:59.473 align:middle line:84%
Don't remember me that way
because that's not who I was.

00:21:59.473 --> 00:22:00.590 align:middle line:90%
That was the old me.

00:22:00.590 --> 00:22:03.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm the young, vital person now.

00:22:03.350 --> 00:22:04.520 align:middle line:90%
That's my spirit.

00:22:04.520 --> 00:22:05.990 align:middle line:90%
Spirit is very, very young.

00:22:05.990 --> 00:22:07.108 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:22:07.108 --> 00:22:08.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I love that guy.

00:22:08.150 --> 00:22:08.900 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I do, too.

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:10.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's spot on, isn't he?

00:22:10.190 --> 00:22:11.440 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Absolutely he is.

00:22:11.440 --> 00:22:14.030 align:middle line:84%
We get to be our perfect
health, our perfect weight.

00:22:14.030 --> 00:22:17.670 align:middle line:84%
If we had glasses, we
don't have them anymore--

00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:20.510 align:middle line:90%
and be our best selves.

00:22:20.510 --> 00:22:23.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The
afterlife-- who made it?

00:22:23.870 --> 00:22:24.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Who knows?

00:22:24.830 --> 00:22:26.900 align:middle line:84%
That's one of those
big questions like,

00:22:26.900 --> 00:22:28.950 align:middle line:84%
what came first-- the
chicken or the egg?

00:22:28.950 --> 00:22:29.750 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:22:29.750 --> 00:22:30.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: God?

00:22:30.550 --> 00:22:34.220 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: For me, I
say God, but it's not

00:22:34.220 --> 00:22:37.070 align:middle line:84%
a guy sitting with
a robe in a chair.

00:22:37.070 --> 00:22:39.860 align:middle line:84%
There is this universal
energy, this life force,

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:43.100 align:middle line:84%
this light that goes
through everything.

00:22:43.100 --> 00:22:45.470 align:middle line:84%
I've done enough experiments
with remote viewing,

00:22:45.470 --> 00:22:47.480 align:middle line:84%
being able to see something
on somebody's table

00:22:47.480 --> 00:22:50.910 align:middle line:84%
on the other side of the
country or the world.

00:22:50.910 --> 00:22:52.380 align:middle line:90%
We are all connected.

00:22:52.380 --> 00:22:57.290 align:middle line:84%
So whatever that divine energy,
that light, that source is,

00:22:57.290 --> 00:22:58.310 align:middle line:90%
that's what I call God.

00:22:58.310 --> 00:23:03.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When people pass
on, do they stay the same

00:23:03.210 --> 00:23:04.690 align:middle line:90%
as the person they were?

00:23:04.690 --> 00:23:05.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yes.

00:23:05.490 --> 00:23:06.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does their
personality stay the same?

00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:08.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: We have
our personality.

00:23:08.160 --> 00:23:09.270 align:middle line:84%
There have been
plenty of people that

00:23:09.270 --> 00:23:10.710 align:middle line:84%
have come through
medium readings

00:23:10.710 --> 00:23:13.470 align:middle line:90%
with jokes and great things.

00:23:13.470 --> 00:23:16.472 align:middle line:84%
One guy liked to
impersonate Elvis,

00:23:16.472 --> 00:23:18.180 align:middle line:84%
so when he came through
a medium reading,

00:23:18.180 --> 00:23:19.380 align:middle line:90%
he came through as Elvis.

00:23:19.380 --> 00:23:21.315 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, he calls my radio
show every once in awhile.

00:23:21.315 --> 00:23:21.960 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Perfect.

00:23:21.960 --> 00:23:22.760 align:middle line:90%
It's great.

00:23:22.760 --> 00:23:24.390 align:middle line:90%
But yeah, we get to be us.

00:23:24.390 --> 00:23:30.080 align:middle line:84%
I think the extra baggage
we have as far as ego and--

00:23:30.080 --> 00:23:31.370 align:middle line:90%
that stuff gets dropped.

00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:33.230 align:middle line:84%
We get to see a
higher perspective,

00:23:33.230 --> 00:23:34.220 align:middle line:90%
but we get to be us.

00:23:34.220 --> 00:23:36.095 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think of the dream state

00:23:36.095 --> 00:23:37.970 align:middle line:84%
to communicate with
the other side?

00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:39.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: I think
it's good, but I

00:23:39.740 --> 00:23:41.040 align:middle line:90%
don't think we can rely on it.

00:23:41.040 --> 00:23:43.248 align:middle line:84%
I think a lot of the things
that happen in our dreams

00:23:43.248 --> 00:23:47.750 align:middle line:84%
are just our own minds
playing through things

00:23:47.750 --> 00:23:49.070 align:middle line:90%
that happen throughout the day.

00:23:49.070 --> 00:23:53.480 align:middle line:84%
But I do know it happens when
our minds are just quiet,

00:23:53.480 --> 00:23:55.730 align:middle line:84%
and we're in that kind
of in-between state

00:23:55.730 --> 00:23:57.270 align:middle line:84%
that our loved ones
can be with us.

00:23:57.270 --> 00:23:59.690 align:middle line:84%
And so if someone
has a dream, and it's

00:23:59.690 --> 00:24:01.580 align:middle line:84%
kind of scary about
their loved one,

00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:03.680 align:middle line:84%
that's probably
their subconscious.

00:24:03.680 --> 00:24:04.638 align:middle line:90%
But when they wake up--

00:24:04.638 --> 00:24:06.055 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Playing
tricks with them.

00:24:06.055 --> 00:24:08.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --and it's so real,
and they can feel the love,

00:24:08.810 --> 00:24:12.860 align:middle line:84%
and they can remember it very
clearly, that could very well

00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.390 align:middle line:90%
be their loved one stopping by.

00:24:14.390 --> 00:24:17.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Some people say that
their loved ones have never

00:24:17.240 --> 00:24:19.980 align:middle line:84%
communicated with them
after they've died.

00:24:19.980 --> 00:24:21.000 align:middle line:90%
Why is that?

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:22.958 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Well, I
think a couple of reasons.

00:24:22.958 --> 00:24:27.480 align:middle line:84%
I think one is we have
free will, living life.

00:24:27.480 --> 00:24:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes our loved
ones may feel that they

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:31.610 align:middle line:90%
don't want to get involved.

00:24:31.610 --> 00:24:33.940 align:middle line:84%
And the other thing
is they say there's

00:24:33.940 --> 00:24:36.710 align:middle line:90%
no time in the other world.

00:24:36.710 --> 00:24:39.160 align:middle line:84%
It's as if 30 years
for you and me

00:24:39.160 --> 00:24:40.733 align:middle line:90%
is a blink of an eye for them.

00:24:40.733 --> 00:24:41.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Like a dream.

00:24:41.650 --> 00:24:43.360 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah,
so they know we're

00:24:43.360 --> 00:24:44.950 align:middle line:84%
going to be together
in just a moment,

00:24:44.950 --> 00:24:46.450 align:middle line:84%
and there's actually
a third reason.

00:24:46.450 --> 00:24:48.460 align:middle line:84%
I think sometimes
they're giving signs,

00:24:48.460 --> 00:24:50.980 align:middle line:84%
and we are so busy either
looking at our phones

00:24:50.980 --> 00:24:53.500 align:middle line:84%
or on the computer or being
in our own head worried

00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:56.470 align:middle line:84%
about the future, that there
could be a license plate

00:24:56.470 --> 00:24:58.810 align:middle line:84%
right in front of us with
our loved one's name on it,

00:24:58.810 --> 00:25:02.745 align:middle line:84%
big rainbow in the sky, all
kinds of things happening,

00:25:02.745 --> 00:25:04.120 align:middle line:84%
but they're not
looking for that.

00:25:04.120 --> 00:25:05.578 align:middle line:84%
They're looking
for something else.

00:25:05.578 --> 00:25:08.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The average person
looks at their smartphone 96

00:25:08.470 --> 00:25:09.520 align:middle line:90%
times a day.

00:25:09.520 --> 00:25:10.640 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Wow.

00:25:10.640 --> 00:25:11.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That seems low to me.

00:25:11.890 --> 00:25:13.720 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: It does
seem low to me too.

00:25:13.720 --> 00:25:16.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I had a buddy of
mine who has passed on.

00:25:16.360 --> 00:25:18.318 align:middle line:84%
He would look at his
phone every three minutes.

00:25:18.318 --> 00:25:19.568 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Oh, that's crazy.

00:25:19.568 --> 00:25:20.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Every three minutes.

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:23.650 align:middle line:90%
So what's 3 divided into 1 hour?

00:25:23.650 --> 00:25:24.590 align:middle line:90%
20.

00:25:24.590 --> 00:25:26.290 align:middle line:90%
20 times an hour.

00:25:26.290 --> 00:25:28.540 align:middle line:90%
Eight hours-- that's 160 times.

00:25:28.540 --> 00:25:30.040 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: But
our loved ones come

00:25:30.040 --> 00:25:32.620 align:middle line:84%
through when our mind
is quiet, and they come

00:25:32.620 --> 00:25:35.510 align:middle line:90%
through using our imagination.

00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:38.650 align:middle line:84%
So if we're so busy
looking at our phone

00:25:38.650 --> 00:25:41.712 align:middle line:84%
or thinking about things,
they can't get through.

00:25:41.712 --> 00:25:43.420 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you've
ever been driving,

00:25:43.420 --> 00:25:46.000 align:middle line:84%
and you just kind of
feel somebody with you.

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:48.560 align:middle line:84%
Or every so often, out
of the corner of my eye,

00:25:48.560 --> 00:25:50.800 align:middle line:90%
I feel or see my grandmother.

00:25:50.800 --> 00:25:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's easy to say, oh,
that's just my imagination.

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:55.572 align:middle line:90%
But that's how they work.

00:25:55.572 --> 00:25:57.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I had a call
from a truck driver

00:25:57.280 --> 00:26:01.240 align:middle line:84%
one night on "Coast to Coast,"
and he said, George, you're not

00:26:01.240 --> 00:26:02.410 align:middle line:90%
going to believe this story.

00:26:02.410 --> 00:26:05.640 align:middle line:84%
And I said, yeah,
I probably will.

00:26:05.640 --> 00:26:12.000 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'm driving on a very
curvy, cliffy road in my truck,

00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:15.000 align:middle line:90%
semi, and I'm exhausted.

00:26:15.000 --> 00:26:17.520 align:middle line:90%
I shouldn't have been driving.

00:26:17.520 --> 00:26:23.290 align:middle line:84%
I doze off going around
these windy, cliffy roads.

00:26:23.290 --> 00:26:29.950 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I woke up, and I
was ready to go over the cliff.

00:26:29.950 --> 00:26:33.970 align:middle line:90%
A hand grabs my steering wheel.

00:26:33.970 --> 00:26:38.140 align:middle line:84%
I already got my two hands
on it, but I'm half asleep.

00:26:38.140 --> 00:26:43.240 align:middle line:84%
A hand grabs it and turns
me back onto the road.

00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:46.320 align:middle line:84%
I was headed right
off the cliff.

00:26:46.320 --> 00:26:48.500 align:middle line:90%
I stopped my truck.

00:26:48.500 --> 00:26:50.270 align:middle line:90%
I woke up.

00:26:50.270 --> 00:26:52.340 align:middle line:84%
I look around, and
there's nobody there.

00:26:52.340 --> 00:26:53.390 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Right.

00:26:53.390 --> 00:26:55.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whose hand was it?

00:26:55.370 --> 00:26:57.403 align:middle line:84%
Who steps in to do
things like that?

00:26:57.403 --> 00:26:58.820 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: If
you want to call--

00:26:58.820 --> 00:26:59.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It wasn't his.

00:26:59.330 --> 00:27:01.980 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --them angels,
but I've heard so many stories

00:27:01.980 --> 00:27:02.780 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:27:02.780 --> 00:27:04.697 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: About your
dearly departed loved one.

00:27:04.697 --> 00:27:06.530 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah,
absolutely, they can.

00:27:06.530 --> 00:27:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think, like I said,
they can mess with free will,

00:27:10.370 --> 00:27:13.760 align:middle line:84%
but there are times where
they can be involved,

00:27:13.760 --> 00:27:16.400 align:middle line:84%
and there's plenty
of stories, though,

00:27:16.400 --> 00:27:20.763 align:middle line:84%
of people who have had these
angels that have helped them.

00:27:20.763 --> 00:27:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And then no one else
has witnessed them,

00:27:22.430 --> 00:27:25.490 align:middle line:84%
but they've saved their life,
because their time wasn't up.

00:27:25.490 --> 00:27:27.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you like
the fact that you

00:27:27.350 --> 00:27:30.020 align:middle line:90%
can dabble with the afterlife?

00:27:30.020 --> 00:27:31.280 align:middle line:90%
Is it enjoyable to you?

00:27:31.280 --> 00:27:33.470 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: It's enjoyable.

00:27:33.470 --> 00:27:35.960 align:middle line:84%
It's something I
love investigating.

00:27:35.960 --> 00:27:38.205 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's some crazy
things out there, so--

00:27:38.205 --> 00:27:39.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what do
you mean by crazy?

00:27:39.830 --> 00:27:42.038 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Well, I don't--
it's like you don't want

00:27:42.038 --> 00:27:43.860 align:middle line:84%
to throw the baby out
with the bathwater.

00:27:43.860 --> 00:27:44.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:27:44.660 --> 00:27:46.550 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: There's
some-- I totally

00:27:46.550 --> 00:27:50.330 align:middle line:84%
believe in trance communication,
some of these mediums

00:27:50.330 --> 00:27:53.230 align:middle line:84%
that can speak on behalf
of somebody who's lived.

00:27:53.230 --> 00:27:54.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:27:54.030 --> 00:27:57.320 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: But I also think
our subconscious mind is

00:27:57.320 --> 00:28:00.740 align:middle line:84%
very powerful, and it's
very easy for somebody

00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:03.440 align:middle line:84%
to close their eyes
and to say things.

00:28:03.440 --> 00:28:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And I've witnessed some
folks that, in my gut,

00:28:07.220 --> 00:28:09.080 align:middle line:90%
I just don't feel as truthful.

00:28:09.080 --> 00:28:10.647 align:middle line:90%
But I--

00:28:10.647 --> 00:28:12.365 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You think
they made up stories?

00:28:12.365 --> 00:28:13.490 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Whether
they made up stories

00:28:13.490 --> 00:28:15.410 align:middle line:84%
or they believe it
themselves, I think

00:28:15.410 --> 00:28:17.100 align:middle line:90%
our minds can be very important.

00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:19.760 align:middle line:84%
So I say to people,
look for your own truth.

00:28:19.760 --> 00:28:23.030 align:middle line:84%
What I say in my book
and on the podcast

00:28:23.030 --> 00:28:26.960 align:middle line:84%
may not fit for everyone, but
if it resonates with your soul,

00:28:26.960 --> 00:28:27.920 align:middle line:90%
follow it.

00:28:27.920 --> 00:28:30.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do we get
signs from the other side

00:28:30.200 --> 00:28:33.980 align:middle line:84%
that our loved ones are out
there communicating with us?

00:28:33.980 --> 00:28:35.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Well,
there's different ways.

00:28:35.960 --> 00:28:37.940 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, through
our imagination,

00:28:37.940 --> 00:28:41.360 align:middle line:84%
you could smell your
grandmother's apple pie or pipe

00:28:41.360 --> 00:28:43.610 align:middle line:90%
your father used to smoke.

00:28:43.610 --> 00:28:45.800 align:middle line:84%
I know people say,
I see feathers,

00:28:45.800 --> 00:28:46.850 align:middle line:90%
and that must be a sign.

00:28:46.850 --> 00:28:48.230 align:middle line:84%
But we have to be
careful of that

00:28:48.230 --> 00:28:50.920 align:middle line:84%
too, because there could be a
bird around the corner that--

00:28:50.920 --> 00:28:51.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: There could be.

00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:52.820 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --didn't make it.

00:28:52.820 --> 00:28:53.620 align:middle line:90%
Music--

00:28:53.620 --> 00:28:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You did a
documentary on a woman

00:28:55.430 --> 00:28:57.527 align:middle line:90%
by the name of Sonia Rinaldi.

00:28:57.527 --> 00:28:58.610 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: That's right.

00:28:58.610 --> 00:29:00.210 align:middle line:90%
It's still in the works.

00:29:00.210 --> 00:29:01.085 align:middle line:90%
It's almost complete.

00:29:01.085 --> 00:29:02.085 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But who is she?

00:29:02.085 --> 00:29:03.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Sonia
is a scientist

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:06.020 align:middle line:84%
who's been in Brazil,
lives in Brazil.

00:29:06.020 --> 00:29:10.940 align:middle line:84%
For over 30 years, she's been
interested in the afterlife.

00:29:10.940 --> 00:29:13.880 align:middle line:84%
I had heard about her at
a conference forever ago,

00:29:13.880 --> 00:29:17.030 align:middle line:84%
and I thought, ooh, I want
to meet this woman someday.

00:29:17.030 --> 00:29:20.390 align:middle line:84%
At those times,
back in the day, she

00:29:20.390 --> 00:29:23.540 align:middle line:84%
would have two chairs
set up and a third chair.

00:29:23.540 --> 00:29:26.360 align:middle line:84%
She'd have a mom,
herself, and a chair

00:29:26.360 --> 00:29:28.090 align:middle line:90%
for the child in the afterlife.

00:29:28.090 --> 00:29:29.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: An empty chair.

00:29:29.090 --> 00:29:30.257 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: An empty chair.

00:29:30.257 --> 00:29:33.260 align:middle line:84%
She would play a
recording of gibberish,

00:29:33.260 --> 00:29:35.930 align:middle line:84%
chopped up human
voices, all rearranged.

00:29:35.930 --> 00:29:36.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:29:36.770 --> 00:29:38.312 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: She'd
talk to the parent

00:29:38.312 --> 00:29:40.790 align:middle line:84%
and say, talk as if
your child's here.

00:29:40.790 --> 00:29:42.620 align:middle line:90%
This is all experimentation.

00:29:42.620 --> 00:29:44.870 align:middle line:84%
She has never charged
a penny for her work.

00:29:44.870 --> 00:29:46.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That had to be
emotional for the parent.

00:29:46.160 --> 00:29:47.327 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Very emotional.

00:29:47.327 --> 00:29:50.150 align:middle line:84%
And for thousands of
parents who sat with her,

00:29:50.150 --> 00:29:52.520 align:middle line:84%
when she played back
that tape recording,

00:29:52.520 --> 00:29:56.180 align:middle line:84%
not only did the parents'
voice beyond their speaking,

00:29:56.180 --> 00:29:58.280 align:middle line:84%
but you would hear
the child's response.

00:29:58.280 --> 00:29:59.134 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Answering?

00:29:59.134 --> 00:29:59.990 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Answering.

00:29:59.990 --> 00:30:00.790 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:30:00.790 --> 00:30:03.590 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: So I knew
someday, I wanted to meet her.

00:30:03.590 --> 00:30:04.880 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That freaks me out.

00:30:04.880 --> 00:30:06.620 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, definitely.

00:30:06.620 --> 00:30:09.710 align:middle line:84%
And then you and I had met
at an afterlife symposium,

00:30:09.710 --> 00:30:12.658 align:middle line:84%
and Sonia happened to be
there showing her new work.

00:30:12.658 --> 00:30:13.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I remember that.

00:30:13.700 --> 00:30:15.290 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And
her new work was

00:30:15.290 --> 00:30:19.190 align:middle line:84%
filming static on a television
or a computer screen

00:30:19.190 --> 00:30:24.390 align:middle line:84%
and having faces show up when
she would play frame by frame.

00:30:24.390 --> 00:30:25.700 align:middle line:90%
So in every second of video--

00:30:25.700 --> 00:30:26.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You had to look.

00:30:26.480 --> 00:30:27.320 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: You had to look.

00:30:27.320 --> 00:30:28.362 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You had to look.

00:30:28.362 --> 00:30:30.920 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: She would go
through each 32 frames or 64

00:30:30.920 --> 00:30:32.990 align:middle line:84%
or however many are in
a second in a video,

00:30:32.990 --> 00:30:34.460 align:middle line:84%
and there would
be faces in there.

00:30:34.460 --> 00:30:36.380 align:middle line:84%
And she started
Work with parents,

00:30:36.380 --> 00:30:38.900 align:middle line:84%
and the child's
faces were there.

00:30:38.900 --> 00:30:42.530 align:middle line:84%
And it's moved on, so
now she uses, literally,

00:30:42.530 --> 00:30:44.570 align:middle line:90%
a clear Easter egg mold.

00:30:44.570 --> 00:30:46.670 align:middle line:84%
And she's got four
mini projectors

00:30:46.670 --> 00:30:49.340 align:middle line:84%
that all project
static electricity.

00:30:49.340 --> 00:30:53.340 align:middle line:84%
I guess it's static like from
a TV channel that's all static.

00:30:53.340 --> 00:30:56.690 align:middle line:84%
And she'll film it, and
she'll work with a parent.

00:30:56.690 --> 00:30:59.297 align:middle line:84%
And she can do it
remotely as well.

00:30:59.297 --> 00:31:00.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, really?

00:31:00.130 --> 00:31:01.922 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Doesn't
need the parent there.

00:31:01.922 --> 00:31:03.530 align:middle line:84%
She's had scientists
come through.

00:31:03.530 --> 00:31:06.260 align:middle line:84%
Very interesting-- Nikola
Tesla has shown his face.

00:31:06.260 --> 00:31:09.930 align:middle line:84%
He's never been
filmed or recorded

00:31:09.930 --> 00:31:12.310 align:middle line:84%
with a smile on his face,
and lo and beholden, his--

00:31:12.310 --> 00:31:13.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They stole his plans.

00:31:13.560 --> 00:31:14.360 align:middle line:90%
He's not happy.

00:31:14.360 --> 00:31:16.260 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --trans
image, he's smiling.

00:31:16.260 --> 00:31:19.380 align:middle line:84%
But she's got hundreds
if not thousands

00:31:19.380 --> 00:31:21.400 align:middle line:90%
of pictures-- mainly children.

00:31:21.400 --> 00:31:23.700 align:middle line:84%
She works with parents,
again, for free.

00:31:23.700 --> 00:31:26.070 align:middle line:84%
So we're doing a
documentary on her

00:31:26.070 --> 00:31:28.090 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to
have over this winter.

00:31:28.090 --> 00:31:28.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, that's exciting.

00:31:28.710 --> 00:31:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: And
really give people--

00:31:29.940 --> 00:31:30.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And how
can people see it?

00:31:30.750 --> 00:31:32.050 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: --that backbone.

00:31:32.050 --> 00:31:35.018 align:middle line:10%
Well, go to wedontdie.com,
which is my website.

00:31:35.018 --> 00:31:35.976 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Wedontdie.com.

00:31:35.976 --> 00:31:39.178 align:middle line:10%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Mm-hmm, and
that will give the best link

00:31:39.178 --> 00:31:40.095 align:middle line:10%
to where the video is.

00:31:40.095 --> 00:31:40.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Named after
your book, by the way.

00:31:40.650 --> 00:31:41.510 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, very simple.

00:31:41.510 --> 00:31:42.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Here's your book back.

00:31:42.030 --> 00:31:42.770 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Thank
you very much.

00:31:42.770 --> 00:31:43.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I already have my copy.

00:31:43.770 --> 00:31:44.970 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yes, you do.

00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:45.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: My signed copy.

00:31:45.990 --> 00:31:46.560 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: That's right.

00:31:46.560 --> 00:31:47.460 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:31:47.460 --> 00:31:49.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you had an
opportunity to talk to somebody

00:31:49.710 --> 00:31:50.980 align:middle line:90%
on the other side--

00:31:50.980 --> 00:31:52.590 align:middle line:90%
and I'm sure you do--

00:31:52.590 --> 00:31:55.520 align:middle line:84%
but what kind of
questions do you ask?

00:31:55.520 --> 00:31:57.650 align:middle line:84%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Well, it'd
be questions about what

00:31:57.650 --> 00:32:00.110 align:middle line:90%
is life like over there.

00:32:00.110 --> 00:32:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And it's funny
because I actually

00:32:02.450 --> 00:32:04.610 align:middle line:90%
do have an opportunity.

00:32:04.610 --> 00:32:09.090 align:middle line:84%
Every Friday-- a friend of
mine is a trance medium,

00:32:09.090 --> 00:32:10.740 align:middle line:90%
and I met him six years ago.

00:32:10.740 --> 00:32:13.980 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, a
skeptical mind would say,

00:32:13.980 --> 00:32:16.770 align:middle line:84%
this might be this young
man putting on a voice.

00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:19.500 align:middle line:84%
But for the past
year and a half,

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:21.960 align:middle line:84%
on Fridays, we get to
have a very extraordinary

00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:23.340 align:middle line:90%
conversation.

00:32:23.340 --> 00:32:27.090 align:middle line:84%
People can come for free
online and listen and ask

00:32:27.090 --> 00:32:28.060 align:middle line:90%
their questions.

00:32:28.060 --> 00:32:31.210 align:middle line:84%
So the questions are, what
is the afterlife like?

00:32:31.210 --> 00:32:34.890 align:middle line:84%
People that have ended their
own life, do they get punished?

00:32:34.890 --> 00:32:36.540 align:middle line:90%
The answer is no.

00:32:36.540 --> 00:32:42.580 align:middle line:84%
Things about what is life for,
and how does healing work--

00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:45.080 align:middle line:84%
how do we communicate
with our loved ones?

00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:47.680 align:middle line:84%
And I get goosebumps
right now because, for me,

00:32:47.680 --> 00:32:51.558 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to talk about because
I think skeptical minds might

00:32:51.558 --> 00:32:52.600 align:middle line:90%
have a hard time with it.

00:32:52.600 --> 00:32:55.360 align:middle line:84%
But this man, this
gentleman named

00:32:55.360 --> 00:33:00.190 align:middle line:84%
Eric, who died at the end of
the 1800s, never misses a beat,

00:33:00.190 --> 00:33:02.245 align:middle line:90%
never hesitates in conversation.

