00:37:44.180 --> 00:37:47.000 align:middle line:84%
He kept going,
and he hit a curb,

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:50.690 align:middle line:84%
and he flew and landed
on top of a stop sign.

00:37:50.690 --> 00:37:53.690 align:middle line:90%
It severed his torso.

00:37:53.690 --> 00:37:55.070 align:middle line:90%
That's how he died.

00:37:55.070 --> 00:37:59.470 align:middle line:84%
So at the funeral, we're
all looking at the casket.

00:37:59.470 --> 00:38:02.000 align:middle line:84%
They kind of stitched
him up a little bit,

00:38:02.000 --> 00:38:05.560 align:middle line:84%
but you look at this
stark, dead body.

00:38:05.560 --> 00:38:09.290 align:middle line:84%
And it hits you for that
first time, what if that's it?

00:38:09.290 --> 00:38:10.090 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Right.

00:38:10.090 --> 00:38:11.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's over for him.

00:38:11.770 --> 00:38:12.950 align:middle line:90%
It's done.

00:38:12.950 --> 00:38:14.170 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing else.

00:38:14.170 --> 00:38:16.180 align:middle line:84%
And I got to tell
you, Sandra, it

00:38:16.180 --> 00:38:22.480 align:middle line:84%
was the coldest, loneliest
feeling I've ever had.

00:38:22.480 --> 00:38:23.768 align:middle line:90%
I can't explain why.

00:38:23.768 --> 00:38:25.060 align:middle line:90%
>>CHAMPLAIN: Yeah, we're human.

00:38:25.060 --> 00:38:28.010 align:middle line:84%
I don't think we're meant
to understand at all.

00:38:28.010 --> 00:38:29.200 align:middle line:90%
I think it's part of grief.

00:38:29.200 --> 00:38:30.430 align:middle line:90%
We're stunned.

00:38:30.430 --> 00:38:34.690 align:middle line:84%
